<p>I just add another way:</p>

<p>To redirect for any specific page/links of your site to another page, just add this line of code:</p>

<pre><code>&lt;script&gt;
    if(window.location.href == 'old_url')
    {
        window.location.href="new_url";
    }

    // Another URL redirect
    if(window.location.href == 'old_url2')
    {
        window.location.href="new_url2";
    }
&lt;/script&gt;
</code></pre>

<p>For a real life example,</p>

<pre><code>&lt;script&gt;
    if(window.location.href == 'https://old-site.com')
    {
        window.location.href="https://new-site.com";
    }

    // Another URL redirect
    if(window.location.href == 'https://old-site.com/simple-post.html')
    {
        window.location.href="https://new-site.com/simple-post.html";
    }
&lt;/script&gt;
</code></pre>

<p>By using this simple code, you can redirect full site or any single page.</p>
